Let's now calculate the present value of the annuity for the first seven years, considering the givens from the period steps.

$$ \begin{aligned}
\text{Present Value of an Annuity} &=\$1,475\times\dfrac{1-\dfrac{1}{\left(1+0.0075\right)^{84}}}{0.0075}
\\[10pt]
&=\$1,475\times\dfrac{0.466154734}{0.0075}
\\[10pt]
&= \boxed{\bf\$91,677.10}
\end{aligned}$$


Based on our calculation, the present value of the annuity for the first seven years is $91,677.10.

Let's now calculate the present value of the annuity for the eighth to fifteenth year.

$$ \begin{aligned}
\text{Present Value of an Annuity} &=\$1,475\times\dfrac{1-\dfrac{1}{\left(1+0.005\right)^{96}}}{0.005}
\\[10pt]
&=\$1,475\times\dfrac{0.380476091}{0.0050}
\\[10pt]
&= \boxed{\bf\$112,240.45}
\end{aligned}$$

Therefore, the present value of the annuity for the eighth to the fifteenth year is $112,240.45.

Let's now calculate the present value of the eight to fifteenth-year earnings.

$$ \begin{aligned}
\text{PV} &=\dfrac{\$ 112,240.45}{\left(1 + 0.0075\right)^{84}}
\\[10pt]
&=\dfrac{\$ 112,240.45 }{1.873201963}
\\[10pt]
&= \boxed{\bf\$59,919.03}
\end{aligned}$$

Hence, the present value for the eight to fifteenth-year is $59,919.03.
